(15, '‘The Alternative is scary for only wrong doers who will be punished’ – Asiedu Nketia replies NPP', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">He said the fear of appointees of the ruling New Patriotic Party (NPP) is that they shall be duly punished for all their loots, hence John Mahama’s coming is highly scary to them.</p><div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,', 1, 1, '2024-08-30 22:23:43', '2024-08-30 22:23:43', 'thumb_66d22a4fcab4e8.37149243.jpeg', 'NDC', 0, 'The National Chairman of the National Democratic Congress (NDC), Johnson Asiedu Nketia has admonishe');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `content`, `author_id`, `category_id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `thumbnail`, `tags`, `is_featured`, `description`) VALUES
(16, 'Judgement on Walewale NPP Primary set for September 2', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Dr. Tiah Abdul-Kabiru who is the Economic Advisor to the Vice President, closed his case after presenting 10 witnesses who were crossed-examined in court in connection with the case.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Madam Abudu earlier presented her witnesses who were equally crossed examined by defence lawyers.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The trial judge, Justice Richard Kogyapwah, has since directed lawyers involved in the case to file their written addresses by close of Friday August 30, 2024.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">He, therefore, adjourned the case to September 2, 2024 for judgement.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Dr. Tiah Abdul-Kabiru Mahama, polled 343 votes, beating the incumbent MP Lariba Zuweira Abudu who obtained 334 votes.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The court had previously granted a plea by the NPP to resolve the issues related to the Walewale Constituency parliamentary primary out of court.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The NPP noted that settling the case out of court will be the best way to sustain peace and unity in the party ahead of the 2024 general election.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">However, the party could not resolve the matter between the parties, resulting in the continuation of the case at the Tamale High Court.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The Tamale High Court has since ordered Madam Lariba Zuweira Abudu and Dr. Tiah Abdul-Kabiru Mahama not to hold themselves as NPP parliamentary candidates for the Walewale Constituency until the final determination of the case.</p>', 1, 1, '2024-08-30 22:25:34', '2024-08-30 22:25:34', 'thumb_66d22abe9d6a21.28645783.jpg', 'NPP', 0, 'The Tamale High Court presided over by Justice Richard Kogyapwah, has scheduled September 2, 2024, f'),
(17, 'If he declines, he doesn’t identify as a dancehall artiste – Shatta Wale challenges Stonebwoy to dancehall battle', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">In a post shared on his official X (formerly Twitter) page, Shatta Wale issued a formal challenge, calling for a face-off to determine who truly holds the title of “Dancehall King” in Ghana.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Shatta Wale’s post read: “I am issuing a formal challenge to @stonebwoy and his fans to meet me at the Accra Sports Stadium to resolve the ‘Dancehall King’ title dispute.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“If he and his fans decline this invitation, he should refrain from identifying as a Dancehall artiste, as I consider him a Reggae artiste.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“I assure the nation’s leaders that this will be a structured and healthy competition.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“Interested sponsors can contact our management teams.”</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The challenge has sparked widespread interest and anticipation within the Ghanaian music industry, with fans eagerly awaiting Stonebwoy’s response.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Shatta Wale’s direct approach underscores the intensity of the rivalry between the two artists, both of whom have been vying for the top spot in the dancehall genre in Ghana for years.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Should Stonebwoy accept, the showdown at the Accra Sports Stadium could be one of the biggest musical events the country has ever seen.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">However, if he declines, the implications of Shatta Wale’s challenge could reverberate throughout the dancehall community, potentially shifting the balance of power in the genre.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">As the nation waits for Stonebwoy’s decision, the debate over who deserves the Dancehall King crown continues to heat up.</p>', 1, 7, '2024-08-30 22:30:59', '2024-08-30 22:30:59', 'thumb_66d22c039c9cc2.65361568.jpg', 'dancehall', 0, 'Ghanaian dancehall artist, Charles Nii Armah Mensah Jr., popularly known as Shatta Wale, has thrown '),
(18, 'My father raised me out of every pit and hell the enemy put me through – Daniel Duncan-Williams', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">During a recent service at Action Chapel International, his father’s church, Daniel opened up about how his father’s unwavering prayers and support helped him overcome what he said was “pit and hell which the enemy put him through.”</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">With gratitude, Daniel acknowledged the guidance by his guardians and support from his family through all his darkest moment.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“Every pit and every hell that the enemy has taken me through, my father has stood there and raised me out. I thank God for all my family, it is indescribable to explain the feeling that I feel right now just to be with my family. I love all my mothers,” Daniel stated.</p><div><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">The once ‘prodigal son’ shared a message of hope and redemption to young people struggling with drug addiction.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">“Lastly, I want to say for every youth who struggling out there with this disease of addiction, you will overcome it in Jesus’ name. If my father, the Archbishop can overcome and if I can overcome, you will overcome,” he added.</p></div>', 1, 7, '2024-08-30 22:34:04', '2024-08-30 22:34:04', 'thumb_66d22cbc408e80.24004578.jpg', 'church', 0, 'Daniel Duncan-Williams, the youngest son of Archbishop Nicholas Duncan-Williams has shared a heartwa'),
(19, 'My mother wanted to abort me because she was a student – Esther Smith', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Speaking in an interview on Accra FM with Nana Romeo, the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://3news.com/showbiz/my-mother-wanted-to-abort-me-because-she-was-a-student-esther-smith/#\" class=\"google-anno\" style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34) !important; text-decoration: none !important; border: 0px !important; box-shadow: none !important; display: inline !important; float: none !important; margin: 0px !important; outline: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; fill: currentcolor !important;\"><svg viewBox=\"100 -1000 840 840\" width=\"calc(15px - 2px)\" height=\"15px\" style=\"color-scheme: initial !important; forced-color-adjust: initial !important; mask: initial !important; math-depth: initial !important; position: initial !important; position-anchor: initial !important; appearance: initial !important; color: inherit !important; font: initial !important; font-palette: initial !important; font-synthesis: initial !important; inset-area: initial !important; text-orientation: initial !important; text-rendering: initial !important; text-spacing-trim: initial !important; -webkit-font-smoothing: initial !important; -webkit-locale: initial !important; -webkit-text-orientation: initial !important; -webkit-writing-mode: initial !important; writing-mode: initial !important; zoom: initial !important; accent-color: initial !important; place-content: initial !important; place-items: initial !important; place-self: initial !important; alignment-baseline: initial !important; anchor-name: initial !important; animation-composition: initial !important; animation: initial !important; app-region: initial !important; aspect-ratio: initial !important;