ince May 2022. By selling Lukaku, Chelsea have also offloaded his substantial £325,000-a-week wages.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Conte mentioned in a pre-match news conference that Lukaku could make his debut for Napoli in their upcoming match against Parma on Saturday. In related news, Chelsea midfielder Tino Anjorin has also made a move to Serie A, signing a three-year deal with Empoli.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Verdana, BlinkMacSystemFont, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, &quot;Open Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">Meanwhile, Chelsea and Saudi Pro League side Al-Ahli are both in talks to sign Napoli’s star striker, Victor Osimhen, which could help Napoli balance their finances after acquiring Lukaku.</p><div><br></div>', 1, 4, '2024-08-30 22:41:11', '2024-08-30 22:41:11', 'thumb_66d22e673af004.12716184.jpg', 'transfer', 0, 'Napoli have secured the signing of Belgium striker Romelu Lukaku from Chelsea in a £30 million deal.');
