nt; z-index: initial !important;\"></div></div></div></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Now we can do more of the testing and we are testing every malaria case. DG had received some package from public, about 4000 kits of army. 1000 kits of RMIT that are going to distribute. So, if clinician you see a case that has a case of similar to dengue you can test basically,” he said.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The viral infection, transmitted by Aedes mosquitoes, is gradually spreading sporadically across the country. All reported cases have been mild, with only two requiring hospital admission.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Although discussions are ongoing about the potential for vaccines, the Ghana Health Service remains focused on early detection, as the country needs to establish a clear threshold for vaccine use.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“We need to establish clear thresholds to say that when it’s above this level and becomes a big issue. So, I wouldn’t. I’m not saying that it’s clearly an issue of being really endemic. What I’m saying is that you’re more likely to get cases daily across the country if you look for it.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">So, what you’re looking for is that is there a surge in cases? And then we’ll try and make sure that you intervene. But then what is good is that the directions to address malaria, somehow addresses dengue. So, the more effective you are with malaria, the more you also be addressing the issue,” he explained.</p>', 16, 6, '2024-09-06 11:37:46', '2024-09-06 10:43:00', 'thumb_66dacd6a715ee9.97590521.jpg', 'Dengue Fever', 1, 'The World Health Organization (WHO) has supported Ghana’s response to the dengue fever outbreak by p'),
(24, 'Galamsey fight: Akufo-Addo and Bawumia have failed; not politicians – Kofi Adams', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">He said everything rises and falls with leadership, hence President Akufo-Addo and Vice President Dr Mahamudu Bawumia should be held responsible for the current state of affairs.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“When we say politicians have failed, we give comfort to those who are in leadership and have the responsibility to address our problems,” he stated on Key Points on Saturday September 7.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Speaking on the same programme, a private legal practitioner Martin Kpebu stated that President Akufo-Addo never meant to put his presidency on the line for the fight against the illegal mining menace as he pledged.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Addressing a two-day workshop on galamsey for traditional leaders drawn from different parts of the country in Accra Monday, July 11, 2017, President Akufo-Addo said: “I have said it in the Cabinet, and perhaps this is the first time I am making this public, that I am prepared to put my Presidency on the line on this matter.”</p>', 1, 1, '2024-09-07 17:40:39', '2024-09-07 17:40:39', 'thumb_66dc73f76d0439.72591647.jpg', 'galamsey', 1, 'The National Democratic Congress’ (NDC) Member of Parliament for Buem Constituency, Kofi Adams, has '),
(25, '2025 AFCON: Ghana’s qualification hopes hit early stumbling block', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Ghana’s journey to the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) has hit an unexpected roadblock, as the Black Stars suffered a shocking 1-0 defeat at home to Angola at the iconic Baba Yara sports stadium.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">This loss, breaking a 24-year unbeaten record at the venue, has left the four-time AFCON champions in a precarious position, sitting joint bottom of Group E. The match, played under the scorching sun in Kumasi sun, saw a spirited Angolan side capitalise on a defensive lapse in the 93rd minute.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Substitute Milson found himself in the right place at the right time and silenced the usually energetic Ghanaian crowd.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Earlier on Wednesday, Sudan had squeezed past Niger with a 1-0 victory, further complicating Ghana’s path to qualification.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The results leave Angola and Sudan joint top of the group, each with three points, while Ghana and Niger languish at the bottom without a point to their names.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The Black Stars’ performance was a far cry from the dominant displays that fans have come to expect in recent times.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Despite controlling possession for large portions of the game, Ghana struggled to create clear-cut chances, with star players like Thomas Partey and Mohammed Kudus unable to unlock the resolute Angolan defence.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Head coach Otto Addo, facing mounting pressure after the defeat, remained defiant in the post-match press conference.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“The second half makes me very confident we can qualify. The good thing is that it’s all in our hands because we still have to face all the teams in the group.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">His optimism, however, was met with scepticism from sections of fans who threw plastic waste onto the pitch in protest.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The road ahead for Ghana looks challenging. Their next fixture sees them travel to Morocco to face Niger, a team desperate to open their account in the group. This away tie now takes on added significance, with anything less than a win potentially derailing Ghana’s qualification hopes.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">While the Black Stars have consistently qualified for each AFCON since 2004, reaching the final twice, their recent performances have often fallen short of expectations with the team struggling to make it past the group stage.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The last time Ghana failed to qualify for an AFCON was in 2004, a streak that could now be tested. As the qualification campaign unfolds, football fans across Africa will be keeping a close eye on Group E.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The prospect of a major tournament without the Black Stars seems unthinkable, but as this opening day upset proves, in football, nothing can be taken for granted.</p>', 1, 4, '2024-09-07 17:42:59', '2024-09-07 17:42:59', 'thumb_66dc74832b3652.05745964.jpg', 'black stars', 0, 'Ghana\'s AFCON hopes hit roadblock with shocking home defeat to Angola'),
(26, 'Death at O’Reilly SHS: GES condoles with family of deceased student', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">In press release, the GES extended its condolences to the family of the deceased and assured the public that a thorough investigation is underway.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">According to the statement released on September 4, 2024, ” the Director-General of the GES led a team to visit both the school and the bereaved family to offer support. The GES is collaborating closely with the relevant authorities to ensure that all circumstances surrounding the incident are thoroughly investigated.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The Service also confirmed that the situation on the school campus has been stabilized and that measures are being taken to ensure the safety of students and staff.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The GES urged the public to “refrain from making speculative statements and to allow the investigative processes to take their course. The Service pledged to keep the public informed as more details emerge.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">This response comes after a fatal altercation at O’Reilly Senior High School on Monday, September 2, 2024, in which Edward Borketey Sackey, an 18-year-old student, was stabbed to death by a fellow student. The incident reportedly stemmed from a disagreement between Edward and another student from the Visual Arts Department, identified as Godwin, over a trivial matter.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Despite Edward’s attempts to seek help, the confrontation escalated, leading to his death. The incident has sent shockwaves through the school community and beyond, prompting calls for a comprehensive review of safety protocols in schools.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">As investigations continue, the GES has stated its commitment to ensuring that justice is served and that measures are put in place to prevent such tragedies in the future.</p><div data-ad-id=\"409525\" class=\"afw afw-ga afw_ad afwadid-409525  \" style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40); text-align: center; float: none; display: none !important;\"><ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-3177501661880531\" data-ad-slot=\"6425443323\" data-adsbygoogle-status=\"done\" data-ad-status=\"unfilled\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: var(--flex-gray-15); display: block; height: 0px;\"><div id=\"aswift_0_host\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: none; outline: 0px; height: 0px; width: 729px; position: relative; visibility: visible; background-color: transparent; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; opacity: 0;\"><iframe id=\"aswift_0\" name=\"aswift_0\" browsingtopics=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-forms allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation\" width=\"729\" height=\"0\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" vspace=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" allowtransparency=\"true\" scrolling=\"no\" allow=\"attribution-reporting\" src=\"https://googleads.g.doubleclick.net/pagead/ads?gdpr=0&amp;us_privacy=1---&amp;gpp_sid=-1&amp;client=ca-pub-3177501661880531&amp;output=html&amp;h=183&amp;slotname=6425443323&amp;adk=1924272391&amp;adf=779450839&amp;pi=t.ma~as.6425443323&amp;w=729&amp;abgtt=5&amp;fwrn=4&amp;lmt=1725723792&amp;rafmt=11&amp;format=729x183&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2F3news.