(28, 'Election year spending poses upside risk to stability of Cedi – Bank of Ghana', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Also, the central bank said, strong liquidity management and continued Forex auctions are expected to support the forex market.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">However, the BoG said in its Monetary Policy Report, July 2024 that “Fiscal spending amid upcoming elections remains an upside risk to the stability of the cedi.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The report further explained that on the international currency market, the US dollar strengthened in June but has since weakened as investors anticipate a rate cut in September, supported by the decline in inflation in June, and softer-than-expected US economic data.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The pressure on the cedi eased somewhat in June from elevated pressures in May, it said.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The easing pressure, the BoG said, was on the back of the revised regulations on advanced payments for imports by the central bank, and steadfast implementation of the new Cash Reserve Ratio (CRR) regime.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Also, it added positive sentiments from the third tranche of the International Monetary Fund&nbsp; External Credit Facility (IMF ECF), the breakthrough with the external debt restructuring, as well as the Fed’s expected rate cut supported the recovery in the cedi.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“The domestic currency depreciated by 18.6 percent, 17.9 percent, and 16.0 percent against the dollar, the pound, and the euro, respectively, on a year-to-date basis. This was against a depreciation of 22.0 percent, 26.3 percent, and 23.8 percent against the dollar, the pound, and the euro, respectively, during the same period in 2023,” the report said.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The central bank is not the only institution raising concerns about how the elections pose significant risk to the Cedi as Ghana heads into a major election on December 7 this year.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Accounting and auditing firm, Deloitte, earlier issued a caution to&nbsp; the government of Ghana against overspending.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Deloitte said spending beyond the limit could pose a severe threat to the downward trend in inflation and also the improved currency performance.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Headline inflation declined to 22.8% in June 2024 from 23.2% in January 2023, per figures churned out by the Ghana Statistical Service (GSS).</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The downward trend in inflation in 2024 has been largely driven by decrease in non-food inflation, tightening monetary policy, ongoing fiscal consolidation by the government, low volatility of transport fares due to stable crude oil prices, and some base drift effect from previous price increases.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">In its assessment of the 2024 mid-year budget statement, Deloitte indicated that the downward trend recorded in the year-to-date depreciation and inflation further affirms the view that Ghana’s economic recovery process is on track.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">This notwithstanding, it said, the upcoming elections and its potential for increased Government expenditure beyond targeted levels, as well as the recurrent increase demand for dollars ahead of Christmas festivities in the last quarter of the year present risk to the improved currency depreciation and inflation recorded so far.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“Having highlighted the risk to maintaining the positive trajectory noted above, it is important to note that the IMF Programme, whilst serving as a check on Government’s expenditure also provides opportunity to boost Ghana’s foreign reserves.</p><div data-ad-id=\"409525\" class=\"afw afw-ga afw_ad afwadid-409525  \" style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40); text-align: center; float: none; display: none !important;\"><ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-3177501661880531\" data-ad-slot=\"6425443323\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: var(--flex-gray-15); display: block;\"></ins></div><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“This, together with other inflows expected from the World Bank Development Policy Operation (DPO) might help absorb some of the FX shocks associated with the December festivities,” it said.</p>', 1, 5, '2024-09-07 17:49:56', '2024-09-07 17:49:56', 'thumb_66dc7624353969.43296827.jpg', 'Bank of Ghana', 1, 'The Bank of Ghana (BoG) has said that in the outlook, the tight monetary policy stance in Ghana and '),
(29, 'Wa Municipal Hospital orders 19 midwives to refund monies extorted from patients', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">According to multiple reports, a six-member disciplinary committee concluded a probe into complaints of extortion lodged by patients who alleged they were pressured into making unauthorized payments.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The investigation unearthed a pattern of improper practices, including:</p><ul style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); list-style: inside circle; color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><li aria-level=\"1\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">Indiscriminate sale of non-drug medical supplies:</span>&nbsp;The midwives were found to be selling essential supplies like surgical gloves, urinary catheters, urine bags, sanitary pads, and even bed mats to patients in the maternity ward, often without the hospital’s knowledge.</li><li aria-level=\"1\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">Unlawful fee collection:</span>&nbsp;The committee determined that the midwives were collecting unauthorized fees from patients, exceeding established hospital charges.</li><li aria-level=\"1\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">Improper demands:</span>&nbsp;Some midwives reportedly made inappropriate demands for additional payments from patients.</li></ul><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">These practices violate the Ghana Health Service’s code of conduct and disciplinary procedures.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">According to Sampson Abu, the Administrator of Wa Municipal Hospital, the investigation was prompted by a surge in public criticism regarding the midwives’ conduct. Complaints centered around unprofessional behavior towards patients, with the illegal sale of non-drug medical supplies being a particularly concerning issue.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“<em style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">The hospital’s administration has recently received significant public criticism for its awful staff conduct towards customers</em>,” Mr. Abu said in a statement published on Pulse Ghana.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">He emphasized the hospital’s commitment to upholding patient and staff dignity and explained the formation of the investigative committee.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The committee’s findings resulted in the directive for the midwives to refund patients, with amounts ranging from GH¢4 to GH¢286. These reimbursements are part of a series of disciplinary measures aimed at deterring future misconduct, according to the hospital.</p>', 1, 6, '2024-09-07 17:52:58', '2024-09-07 17:52:58', 'thumb_66dc76da247770.65419715.jpg', 'hospital', 0, 'Nineteen (19) midwives at the Wa Municipal Hospital have been ordered to reimburse patients followin'),
(30, '2024/25 Ghana Premier League season preview: Expectations, contenders, and survival battles', '<div class=\"flex max-w-full flex-col flex-grow\" style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><div class=\"min-h-[20px] text-message flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 whitespace-normal break-words [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-5\" dir=\"auto\" data-message-author-role=\"assistant\" data-message-id=\"9662a4f9-1f51-4d16-99a5-7d326ad7654b\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\"><div class=\"flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[3px]\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\"><div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert light\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\"><p style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">The 2024/25 Ghana Premier League season kicks off on September 7, with 18 clubs competing in what promises to be another thrilling campaign.</p><p style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">FC Samartex 1996 will look to defend their title after a surprise victory last season, while giants like Asante Kotoko and Hearts of Oak aim for a return to the top.</p><p style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">As new clubs join the fray, the battle for survival will be just as intense as the race for the crown.</p></div></div></div></div><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">Expectations</span></p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The 2024-25 season is ideally expected to be as feisty as ever, with 18 clubs vying for the ultimate crown. Each team will play a maximum of 34 games across home and away ties, with the team with the most points crowned winners at the end of the season.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">FC Sarmatex clinched the title for the first time at the end of the 2023-24 season, against all odds.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">A total of 305 games were played across all match venues in the 2023-24 season, with 625 goals scored. Home sides accounted for 418 of the goals, whereas away teams scored 207. Additionally, home teams won 178 times, while away sides won 51 times with 76 draws being played. 57 of the goals resulted from spot kicks, whereas 15 of the total 72 penalties were missed.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">A low discipline record meant 1044 yellow cards were handed out to the various players, with 47 red cards as well.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Much is not expected to change In the upcoming season.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">Title Contenders</span></p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Asante Kotoko after their worst finish (6th) in the Premier League for the past five years will be hoping that they can win their 27th league title in the upcoming season.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Hearts of Oak, led by Head coach Abubakar Ouattara, will be aiming to improve on their performances last season and contend for the GPL title alongside rivals Kotoko.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The 2022-23 Premier League champions Medeama are looking forward to bouncing back after a tricky campaign in the 2023-24 season, with their early exit in the CAF Champions League and a poor run of form in the league. Nebojsa Kapor and his players will be in the mix to lift the title at the end of the season.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">First-time winners of the Ghana Premier League, Samartex 1996, are now the team to beat before teams will have a chance of winning the title. Manager Nurudeen Amadu and his players will have to overcome every obstacle to defend their title this season</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">Relegation battle</span></p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Great Olympics, Bofoakwa Tano and Real Tamale United were unfortunate not to survive the drop last term and fell into the Access Bank Division One League.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Three teams were promoted in their stead ( Vision Fc, Basake Holy Stars and Young Apostles Fc). However, two (Basake Holy Stars and Young Apostles) of the three teams are expected to lose their Premier League status at the end of the season.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The step up to the top flight will prove daunting for the teams, who look unlikely to cope with the intensity and demands of the league. Legon cities, who finished just a point to beat the drop last term, are also in the running to go down.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><span style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px;\">The Big Guns</span></p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The two most successive sides (Kumasi Asante Kotoko and Hearts of Oak) will slug it out for the ultimate bragging right. After a massive overhaul by Kumasi Asante Kotoko, parting ways with a little more than 20 players, the Porcupine Warriors are expected to put the troubles of last season behind them, where they finished 6th.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The team amassed the most points (19) on the road last season, with an underwhelming home record (which included five losses, three draws and nine wins ) putting them out of contention for the league.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Kotoko have signed 13 players, and with a tweak in home form, the Porcupine Warriors should challenge for their 27th crown. Meanwhile, Hearts of Oak’s points tally of 45 was enough to keep them in the league after Olympics were relegated with 45 points.</p><div data-ad-id=\"409525\" class=\"afw afw-ga afw_ad afwadid-409525  \" style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40); text-align: center; float: none; display: none !important;\"><ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-3177501661880531\" data-ad-slot=\"6425443323\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: var(--flex-gray-15); display: block;\"></ins></div><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">With a relatively decent pre-season, winning one game, drawing five, and losing one, Hearts under Aboubakar Ouattara are expected to compete for domestic honours this season.</p>', 1, 4, '2024-09-07 17:55:32', '2024-09-07 17:55:32', 'thumb_66dc777451ee57.31936930.jpeg', 'kotoko', 0, 'With 18 clubs set to clash in the 2024/25 season, the race for the title is on as big guns Kotoko an'),
(31, 'New metering system is helping to bring down the losses to about 26.9% – ECG MD', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">He stated that the loopholes in the system were accounting for the huge losses experienced by the ECG&nbsp; but the trend is changing gradually with the introduction of the new metering system.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The Electricity Company of Ghana (ECG) suffered a GH¢10.21 billion loss in 2022, worse than the GH¢1.91 billion recorded in 2021.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">It represents more than 433 per cent loss in 2022 due largely to exchange rate losses resulting from the cedi depreciation and increased cost of distributing power to consumers.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">This came at a time when some consumers across the country complained of intermittent power supply which led many of them to endure prolonged periods of darkness and disruption in their daily lives.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The power distributor’s losses were captured in the Auditor General’s Report on the account of public boards, corporations and other statutory institutions in 2023.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Speaking in an interview with TV3’s Kemmini Amanor in a yet-to-be-aired interview on the Hot Issues, Mr Dubik Mahama said “We are trying to plug the loopholes in the system. We want our customers to have confidence in the work that we are doing.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">He added, ” the new metering system has helped us bring down our losses to about 26.9%.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Samuel Dubik Mahama further said that there were several meters in the system that are obsolete. He said about one million meters have outlived their usefulness.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“The current meters are obsolete,” he said.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">He added, “There are categories for replacement of meters…there are over a million meters that have outlived their usefulness.”</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">On the issue of&nbsp; power theft, he said it is still a major problem for the ECG.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">“We are consciously moving our clients to a new system, power theft is still a major issue,” he said.</p><div data-ad-id=\"409525\" class=\"afw afw-ga afw_ad afwadid-409525  \" style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; 