ign: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The breakdown of typical monthly earnings by occupation was as follows:</p><ul style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); list-style: inside circle; color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\"><li style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\">Kayayei (head porters): GH¢ 500</li><li style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\">Street vendors: GH¢ 1,250</li><li style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\">Waste pickers: GH¢ 1,300</li><li style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; position: relative;\">Market traders: GH¢ 2,200</li></ul><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The report further reveals that a typical worker’s household spends more than half of its income on food, leaving little room for other essential expenses like education, transportation, and healthcare. The lack of social safety nets for informal workers, with only 3% enrolled in the three-tier pension scheme in 2020, exacerbates their vulnerability to economic shocks.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">t also found that the cost-of-living crisis is affecting workers in informal employment in a number of ways. For example, the report found that market traders and street vendors are facing lower demand for their products and services. The report also found that waste pickers are facing lower selling prices for the waste they collect. The report also found that kayayei (head porters) are facing lower demand for their services.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The cost-of-living crisis has forced many informal workers to adopt desperate coping mechanisms, such as reducing food consumption, working longer hours, and incurring debt. The report also highlights the negative impact on the physical and mental health of these workers, who often experience exhaustion, malnutrition, insomnia, and anxiety.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">WIEGO calls on the government to take immediate action to support informal workers, including providing cash grants and soft loans, controlling inflation on essential items, and recognizing the workplaces of informal workers as legitimate sites of work. It also emphasizes the need to invest in the occupational health and safety of these workers and remove barriers to accessing healthcare.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing, 1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The WIEGO report serves as a stark reminder of the harsh realities faced by informal workers in Accra. It is a call to action for policymakers and stakeholders to address the urgent needs of this vulnerable population and ensure their economic resilience in the face of the ongoing cost-of-living crisis.</p>', 1, 5, '2024-09-08 14:45:21', '2024-09-08 14:45:21', 'thumb_66dd9c610d0649.49205688.jpeg', 'Inflation', 0, 'The cost-of-living crisis in Accra, Ghana, has had a significant impact on informal workers, accordi'),
(41, '2025 AFCON qualifiers: Victor Osimhen closing in on goalscoring record', '<p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Nigeria forward Victor Osimhen has moved into second place in the all-time Nigerian goalscoring chart after coming off the bench to score in the Super Eagles’ 2025 AFCON qualifier against Benin on Saturday.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Osimhen, who was at the heart of multiple transfer sagas with his club (Napoli), was omitted from the Italian side’s squad for the 2024-25 season.</p><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">The Napoli outcast then agreed a loan move with Turkish outfit Galatasaray until the end of the season, although there is a break clause option in his contract, which will see the forward be given permission to leave the club in January if a team matches Napoli’s valuation of him.The ongoing feud between the club and Osimhen meant the Nigerian was yet to feature in a competitive game since May 26.</p><div><span style=\"color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">However, six minutes into replacing Victor Boniface, Osimhen volleyed home a Wilfred Ndidi cross to extend Nigeria’s lead to 2-0 over Benin, before Ademola Lookman sealed the victory seven minutes from time.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(40, 40, 40); font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">The 78th minute finish sees Osimhen draw level with Segun Odegbami in second place on 22 goals for the Super Eagles, moving one clear of Yakubu Anyebeni and 15 behind Rashidi Yekini’s record.</span><br></div><p style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40);\">Osimhen will look to further close in on Yekini’s 37 goal haul when Nigeria face Rwanda on Tuesday in the second qualifying group game.</p><div data-ad-id=\"409525\" class=\"afw afw-ga afw_ad afwadid-409525  \" style=\"font-family: Oxygen, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; margin-block-start: 0px; margin-block-end: var(--cp-spacing,1.5rem); color: rgb(40, 40, 40); text-align: center; float: none; display: none !important;\"><ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-3177501661880531\" data-ad-slot=\"6425443323\" data-adsbygoogle-status=\"done\" data-ad-status=\"unfilled\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; outline: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: var(--flex-gray-15); display: block; height: 0px;\"><div id=\"aswift_1_host\" style=\"font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; line-height: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: none; outline: 0px; height: 0px; width: